(26, 'Residential Mortgage', 'Loan', '<p>Purchasing your first home or a new home could be one of the most rewarding experiences in your life. Monest would give you a hand when you are facing various choices, and help you make an optimal decision, which would make a positive impact for your future life.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul class="nav nav-tabs">\r\n	<li class="active"><a data-toggle="tab" href="#home">Home Buyer</a></li>\r\n	<li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#menu1">Renewals and Transfers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#menu2">Self Employed</a></li>\r\n	<li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#menu3">Non-resident to buy a house loan process</a></li>\r\n	<li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#menu4">New Immigrants</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-content">\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade in active" id="home">&nbsp;\r\n<h4><b>Home Buyer</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Moving through the following 7 steps to purchase your first home can be greatly streamlined with the expert help of Urban Mortgage and other professionals by your side.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Step 1: Get Pre-approved</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;A pre-approval is a must in the fast paced real estate market in Alberta. A mortgage pre-approval will determine the maximum amount you will be approved for. It will also hold the interest rate for you while you shop, ensuring that you receive the best mortgage rates possible when it comes time to make your offer. Urban Mortgage pre-approvals generally take 2 business hours to complete, and give you the benefit of the best mortgage rates in Canada. You can even apply online.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Step 2: Arrange Your Down Payment</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; If you are taking advantage of the Home Buyers Plan, you should make sure that you have notified your financial advisor about your plans to purchase. You will then be required to fill out a T1036 form from Revenue Canada. Your financial advisor or tax office can supply you with this form. Receipt of your funds may take some time so it is important that you request your funds early on in your home buying process. If your down payment is coming in the form of a &ldquo;Gift,&rdquo; you will be required to supply proof in the form of a letter that states who is gifting you the money and what it will be used for.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Step 3: Hire an Experienced Realtor</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; Having an experienced realtor guide you through this market can make the experience of purchasing your home a lot easier. An experienced realtor will be able to help you find the home of your dreams while negotiating the best price for you. monest Financial partners with some of the top real estate agents in Ontario.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Step 4: Hire a Home Inspector</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Home inspectors are a great resource to ensure that your new home purchase is not only a house you get to live in but also a sound and safe investment. With a report from a home inspector, you will be able to see the full extent of any damages or deficiencies that may not be visible in your new home.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Step 5: Have All Your Documents Ready</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;From your mortgage approval to the purchase contract, there are many documents you will need to sign and provide to complete the transaction. Your Urban Mortgage agent will guide you on the exact documents you will need to obtain a mortgage commitment. Below is a list of the most common documents required: Employment Letter Most Recent pay stub Statements indicating where the down payment is coming from. In the case of a 5% down payment mortgage, lenders may require that you provide three months history on the down payment. With a 5% down payment, you will also be required to provide proof that you have 1.5% of the purchase price for closing costs Purchase Contract and all amendments Void cheque Copy of drivers license and another piece of ID</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Step 6: Hire a Real Estate Lawyer</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; A real estate lawyer can legally advise you on your rights as a buyer while guiding you through the purchase contract and mortgage documents. A good real estate lawyer will also be able to explain to you in simple language the legal jargon found in contracts. Meet with your lawyer prior to your closing or possession date. Generally, your real estate lawyer will want to meet with you one month before your closing date. No matter where you are in Ontario, contact us for a list of lawyers in your area.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Step 7: Move In</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;You&#39;ve found the house, you have your mortgage in place, and all conditions have been removed. It&rsquo;s time to plan your move: If you plan on hiring a mover, now is the time to do so since movers book up very quickly. Give notice to your current landlord. Start the process of contacting your family members and creditors to provide them with your new address. Call your local utility companies to set up an account as well as informing them of your move in date.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade" id="menu1">&nbsp;\r\n<h4><b>Renewals and Transfers</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; When a term is coming to a close, most Canadian banks will send a mortgage renewal notice in the mail usually one to two months prior to the term expiration. At this time the banks tend to take advantage of our busy schedules to assume that you will sign on with them for another term.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><b>Renewals and Transfers</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>The worst part is that the banks only tend to offer you their posted rate with very little or no discount. Almost 60 percent of the public sign this renewal without researching what the competition has to offer. We, at monest, are here to offer you the expertise and resources so you can take advantage of the competitive mortgage market. Let us shop your mortgage renewal to find you the best deal. It may be your bank or another lender, and the difference in rates can be significant. We could save you thousands over the term of your mortgage. It costs you nothing but a phone call and we walk you through the process. Don&rsquo;t take your biggest investment for granted. Be certain you are getting the best deal on your mortgage renewal. In addition to low mortgage rates, we can find you a mortgage product that suits your lifestyle and needs. Need flexibility with payments? Not sure if variable or fixed is better for you? Want to renew for a higher amount? We can answer all your mortgage renewal questions with unbiased, expert advice. Let us &lsquo;Taylor make&rsquo; a mortgage renewal to suit your needs and save you money.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade" id="menu2">&nbsp;\r\n<h4><b>Self Employed</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; Over 20% of Canadian income earners are self employed, business for self or are 100% commissioned. With this large of a segment of the population working for themselves you would think the mortgage banks in Canada would be a little more accommodating. Well they have! Finally. Most people in business write off expenses before declaring their income. That&#39;s the advantage of being in business for yourself. You pay income tax on a lesser amount but when you need to prove income for a mortgage approval, your tax returns make it look like your income is low and you can&#39;t afford the mortgage you deserve. Qualifying for a Low Documentation Mortgage is easier than you think. You can purchase a new property or re-finance your existing home up to 90% of its appraised value. The lender bases their mortgage approval on your good credit history instead of your net income. At monest Mortgage we understand your needs. Our lenders look at your credit history rather than business financials and personal tax notice of assessments. This is something most mortgage lenders won&#39;t do. With monest and our preferred lenders, you will find a product that is right for you.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4><b>No Income Mortgage</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; With the No Income Mortgage, you can purchase a new property or re-finance your existing home up to 75% of its appraised value. Income and credit do not have tobe perfect. With 25% down or at least 25% equity CanEquity can obtain a mortgage for almost any income or credit situation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please remember each application is unique and these are just some examples of the current products available to business-for-self persons. Here are a few things to remember when shopping for a mortgage: A self-employed person with a clean credit history in most cases will receive the lowest rates available. Although an established credit history does improve your interest rate, it is not a requirement for obtaining a mortgage. Please keep in mind that the property must be in or near a major center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade" id="menu3">&nbsp;\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Over the years, with the Canadian government&#39;s policy of tourism, family visits, study and work visa relaxation, more and more non-residents choose to invest in Canada to buy a house. Non-Canadian residents to buy a house in general there are three cases:<br />\r\nFirst, parents to study in Canada for children to buy a house, so when children do not have to rent a house, parents are more assured and worry, after the child learn if left, but also save the trouble to buy a house. If the child learn to leave, put the house to sell, short-term home buyers may also get investment income. Second, is the person who is preparing to apply for Canadian settlements, although the immigrants have not yet fully run, but if that market is on the rise, suitable for investment, early purchase of property, both hedging and value-added potential, apply for immigration process is also possible Plus points, future migration here also has a place to live. The third is that their own people are not in Canada, there is no immigration plan, children are not studying in Canada, but the funds are relatively wealthy, and because Canada is a beautiful living environment, as well as a stable economic market, investment in recent years, real estate The return is not low, so I hope to invest in Canada&#39;s real estate to return, for the future if the settlement abroad to do a plan.<br />\r\nCompared with the domestic lending rate, the Canadian loan interest rate is lower than half, so even with sufficient funds on hand, many investors still want to seek bank loans to buy a house to get the maximum return on investment.<br />\r\nSo how does a non-resident buy a house in Canada? First of all to choose a trusted real estate broker, in Canada, real estate agents are registered in the local real estate and subject to the relevant legal constraints, the Canadian investment in the operation of the purchase and China is different from the vast majority of houses are hanging on the website Open sale, that is all the agents face the Canadian investment and purchase housing is basically the same, so the housing is very natural when the price constraints by the market, driving up the behavior of the house is almost impossible.<br />\r\nWhen the house is submitted, the person who buys the house can not be in Canada. Many non-residents bought the Canadian property, they returned home. Some people may not be able to come to Canada for housekeeping and loan procedures because of this or that reason. There are two ways to solve the problem of delivery. First, the power of attorney, that is, Power Of Attorney, referred to as POA. After buying a house, a housekeeper can sign a power of attorney in a Canadian law firm, entrust a relative or friend to handle the collection and loan procedures. The second is to find a Canadian law firm that can provide services in the country.<br />\r\nHowever, it should be noted that some banks do not recognize POA as a loan document, this time in the application for loans when you need to ask your loan broker. It should be noted that buyers of real estate agents or lawyers are not allowed to become a buyer POA by the client. There are POA usually need to handle in Canada, that is, even if the client is a non-resident, in most cases also need to visit Canada for a trip to the formalities. Non-resident loans, first of all need to open an account in the Canadian bank, the account is used to deposit the necessary down payment for the purchase of funds, and to pay the amount of money required for each month. Usually the bank will ask the house to transfer the 15 working days before the down payment of funds to be in place before the final loan. There are some banks even asked to apply at the time of the need to see the first arrival, or at least one month in advance time. For nonresidents, if you have a work visa and have enough income, you can get up to 90% of the loan, and of course most of the nonresidents are not working in Canada for the record and history, then the bank usually needs non-residents to provide 35 % Down payment.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane fade" id="menu4">&nbsp;\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">For new immigrants, the primary problem is the purchase of new homes. If the asset has not all been transferred to Canada, mortgage is an inevitable choice. New immigrant mortgage process and notes are as follows.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether the bank approves mortgage loans depends on the applicant&#39;s ability to repay. In the case of certain income and no other debt, if you can provide 20% of the price as down payment, the maximum amount of the loan is 5-6 times of the annual income of the family (before tax) according to the current interest rate; If the down payment is less than 20% of the price, the maximum amount of the loan is 4-5 times of the annual income of the family (before tax). The minimum down payment is 5% of price. The new immigrants who resident in Canada less than 5 years will be able to apply for a mortgage loan with 35% down payment, and do not need to verify their income. Canadian financial institutions are almost entirely based on the applicant&#39;s credit report to review the application. Borrowers with serious bad credit records are usually rejected. For new immigrants, there is normally no credit record. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From the purchase process, the first step is to apply for mortgage pre-approval. There are three advantages: 1. After obtaining the mortgage pre-approval document, you can determine the target price. 2. In the interest rate lock period to close the property purchase, usually interest rate lock period is 90-120 days. 3. If there is any problem with the credit record when applying for a pre-approval, you need to remedy it immediately.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Canadian commercial banks on the purchase of the first payment requirements are not the same. If the borrower&#39;s down payment is less than 20% of the market value of the house, the commercial bank will need to purchase the mortgage default insurance (security), and the premium will be paid by the applicant. As for the down payment source and deposit period, each bank is different. Some banks need to check the last three months of bank statements, and some banks require a proof of payment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After signing the purchase contract, the client who has applied for the pre-approval needs to submit the contract to the bank and convert to the official approval. If you do not apply for a pre-approval, it is advisable to set a reserve condition when signing the contract, that is, if you can not obtain the mortgage approval within 5 days, you will have the right to cancel the purchase contract and withdraw the deposit. Need to be reminded that even if the bank is officially approved may also eventually refuse to lend, or change the amount of the loan. The problem is usually in both house conditions and income. The appraiser was commissioned by the bank to find the price seriously deviated from the market value, the loan amount will be re-verified in accordance with the assessment price. If the house has illegally altered or planted marijuana, the bank may even refuse to lend. If the applicant is unable to verify the income at the time of filing the application, the bank will also change the amount of the loan or even refuse to lend. Canadian banks are different from Chinese banks. Loan approval is based on the borrower&#39;s words, and then go to verify whether it is true, So the loan approval is usually one to two days to complete. Therefore, the accuracy of the information requested by the applicant at the time of application is very important. For new immigrants who do not have income, the procedure is very simple. Banks only need to verify the landing time, down payment and house prices can be the whole process 3-10 days to complete.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Interest rates are divided into fixed and variable rates. Fixed rate refers to the same interest rate during the loan period, for example, X%, from the first day, to the loan contract expires, the interest rate is always X%. Another interest rate is the variable rate, which is a parameter plus or minus X%. During the loan period, this parameter will change, but X% does not change, for example P-0.5%, refers to the period of the loan, P ( Primerate rate will change, but -0.5% change. Variable rates are more risky, but are usually lower than fixed rates for the same term.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mortgage can be divided into open and closed. If the borrower chooses an open mortgage, the mortgage can be repaid at any time during the period and the mortgage is lifted without penalty. If you choose a closed, as long as the mortgage does not expire, pay off the loan in advance and lift the mortgage will be fined.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From the above classification can be seen, the Canadian mortgage loans can be divided into fixed-rate closed-end loans, fixed-rate open loans; floating interest rate open loans, and floating rate closed loans. Borrowers can choose according to their actual situation.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Canada, the loan period is different from the payoff period. The borrower can sign a one-year loan contract with the bank, but it is expected that the loan will be repaid for 30 years, that is, the loan period is 1 year and the payoff period is 30 years. After the expiration of the year, the borrower may choose to pay the loan in full, or renew it from the original bank or borrow from the other bank to the original loan bank.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The net value of the house is related to the mortgage loan. That is, the net value of the mortgage to do the consumer credit line. This is a recyclable consumer credit product, due to the net worth as a mortgage, so interest rates is lower than ordinary consumer credit products, such as the car loans, credit card interest rates.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Borrowers can choose their own mortgage payment time, such as by weekly, by bi-weekly, by monthly. The longest interval is monthly payment. The shorter the interval, the more able to save interest.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are three major categories of insurance to buy: loans default insurance, fire insurance (property insurance) and life and injury insurance. If the down payment exceeds 20% of the price, then in most cases will not be required to purchase loan default insurance. The property is a collateral for bank, therefore , borrower must buy fire (property) insurance. If the property has property management fees which already contain fire insurance premiums, borrowers do not need to buy another. Life insurance and injury insurance are optimal insurance for borrower. If the borrower purchases a life insurance related to the mortgage, the insurance company will pay the loan balance once the borrower has a personal accident. If the borrower buys a disability insurance, the insurance company will pay the loan in the event of an injury accident Of the monthly contribution.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Ontario, real estate is done through a lawyer. After the mortgage is finally approved and all the terms are met, the bank will clearly indicate the lawyer. The lawyer will calculate the borrower&#39;s real estate transaction costs and inform the borrower the amount of down payment and deposit to the firm and invites the borrower to sign the document. After the borrower signs the official document, the lawyer will issue a solicitation instruction to the bank. In closing date, The bank will transfer the amount of the loan to the lawyer&rsquo;s trust account. The buyer&#39;s lawyer will transfer full amount into the seller&#39;s account. To complete the settlement work, the buyer received the new house key, and the seller received payment. It should be noted that the borrower signed the mortgage loan document is completed in the firm, rather than signed a loan document in the bank. In other words, only the lawyer in front of the signing of the loan document is valid, previously signed all kinds of documents are not a formal loan contract. Some applicants at the same time in several banks to apply for a mortgage loan, the final law firm will have several loan documents waiting to sign, the borrower to choose which bank documents, the final loan contract is signed with this bank. It should be noted that the borrower will sign the mortgage document in the lawyer&rsquo;s firm. In other words, only the lawyer in front of the signing of the loan document is valid, previously signed all kinds of documents are not a formal loan contract. Some applicants apply for mortgage loans in several banks at the same time. The firm will have several loan documents waiting to be signed and the borrower will choose one of them.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>New immigrants in the absence of income, not only can apply to the housing mortgage loans, also apply to investment in real estate mortgage loans.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Residential Mortgage', 1, 0),
(27, 'Commercial Mortgage', 'Loan', '\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; If you&#39;re looking to purchase or refinance income-producing properties our mortgage company, based in Ontario, specializes in finding solutions to your particular needs. You&#39;ll benefit from our company&#39;s experience and knowledge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; Goldensun Capital Mortgage has various resources for commercial lending. Our agents can arrange a commercial mortgage quickly and conveniently. Why not save yourself the time and let us do the work for you? Commercial mortgages are available to clients who are searching for financing to cover costs for purchases of commercial buildings, fuel stations, multi-family units and apartment buildings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; Commercial lenders have different criteria for each situation. Take advantage of our resources and expertise when it comes to your commercial mortgage. Our agents are always available to discuss your situation and needs for a commercial mortgage.</p>\r\n', '', '', 'Commercial Mortgage', 1, 0),
(28, 'Private Loan', 'Loan', '<p>The most important characteristic of private loan is collateral on the property. Private loan is a type of loan that is similar with the bank loan in nature and form. The difference is that, out of different purposes such as renovation cost, first home or commercial mortgage, or second mortgage, the borrowers need capital to fund their expenditure in a limited time.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><b>What the process of Private Lending is like?</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;We will investigate the borrower&rsquo;s purpose of lending, financial background, credit rating history, and asset appraisal report. The lawyers of both borrower and lender would make sure the legality of the contact.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Goldensun Capital, in this process, is the bridge of both lender and borrower, provide proper suggestions and sufficient resources, make sure the legal and professional services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-6">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><b>How is the security of the investment ensured?</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>The subject property of borrower is the most important collateral for the principal of the lender.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Private Loan', 1, 0),
(29, 'Commercial Leasing', 'Loan', '\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext">Financial Leasing Loans:</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nFinancial leasing companies deposit the money into the bank, and then the bank will be in the form of loans to customers. The customer will pay the rental fee to the financial leasing company.<br />\r\nFinancial leasing:<br />\r\n<strong>(1) also known as equipment leasing or modern leasing<br />\r\n(2) is a lease that transfers all or most of the risks and rewards associated with the ownership of the asset. The ownership of an asset can eventually be transferred or not transferred.<br />\r\n(3) Entrusted loans</strong></p>\r\n', '', '', 'Commercial Leasing', 1, 0),
(30, 'Secondary Mortgage', 'Loan', '<h1><b><sub>Secondary Mortgage</sub></b></h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>Secondary mortgage is a mortgage that has been collateralized and secured from a specific lender. The secondary mortgage is characterized by a lot of intermediate links that do not have to pay off the previous loan, directly re-secured and get the loan again, saving time and the cost of the payment.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a name="1_1"></a><b> <a name="sub3026063_1_1"></a><a name="定义"></a>Definition</b></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, suppose a set of real estate in the bank has done a mortgage, is still a normal repayment, in which case the owner to apply for a mortgage again, do not have to pay off the bank loan in advance. As long as through professional assessment, the property can be re-mortgaged according to the assessed value.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a name="1_2"></a><b> <a name="sub3026063_1_2"></a><a name="额度"></a>Quota</b></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Applicants can only do a mortgage registration and get the highest amount of mortgage loans. After the maximum loan amount is obtained, the borrowing can be made several times according to the need, and the interest calculation time is based on the actual payment time of each payment. This can save a lot of unnecessary interest costs. Generally, commercial banks do the highest amount of mortgages.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a name="1_3"></a><b> <a name="sub3026063_1_3"></a><a name="余额抵押"></a>Residual mortgage</b></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Secondary mortgage is the residual mortgage. In accordance with the provisions of the law, as long as a mortgage, The second mortgage is secured by the balance of the house. Common forms of secondary mortgage are Five-color soil mortgage, pawn mortgage or professional loan company mortgage.</p>\r\n', '', '', 'Secondary Mortgage', 1, 0),
(31, 'Mortgage Refinancing', 'Loan', '\r\n<h4><b>Mortgage Refinancing</b></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p>Canadians may borrow for different reasons &ndash; job loss, education, home renovations, large purchases, etc. The valuable equity that you may already have in your home can be used to consolidate high interest credit card debts, credit lines and even car loans. Pulling equity out of your home at today&#39;s great interest rates can save you as much as 17% a month in interest charges! In the past, for a client to consolidate credit card and loan debts, a second mortgage was your only choice. Did you know second mortgage rates can be as high as 19%? Since secured home loans are based on the equity in your home, they are considered low risk by lenders. Therefore, you can use the low interest loans or lines of credit to pay off high interest credit cards and debts. By consolidating debt, you can also free up cash flow. Using one low interest loan to pay off several high interest loans will mean you only make one debt payment a month.</p>\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Refinancing', 1, 0),
(32, 'Mortgage Pre-approval', 'Loan', '<p class="new-customtext">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext"><strong>Mortgage pre-approval -Canadian purchase permission</strong></h4>\r\n<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\nAre we getting the mortgage first or looking for the property? Different people have different opinions on this subject. With the mortgage pre-approval, You can strive for no loan terms of the offer, so that you are more advantages than other competitors.<br />\r\nShowings and apply for loans, the former sounds more exciting, while the latter is to give people the feeling of oppression or tension. As a serious consideration for the family to buy a house, mortgage pre-approval application is indeed a cramped and disturbing things. Before the application, you need to collect a variety of financial sources to see how much can come up with the down payment, to check how much the debt you owe, to get the perfect employment letter from the employer, to get the credit records, and to contact with banks or mortgage brokers. Another advantage of the mortgage pre-approval is that you can lock the interest rate in advance. When interest rates rise, enjoy the already low interest rates. When interest rates fall, you may still get lower interest rates, which is the advantage of locking interest rates.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\nIt is very important to understand your credit report when applying for a loan. There are many applicants who have credit problems, but most of them do not know that they have. A few years ago the phone arrears; credit card late payment; credit investigation agency mistaken information; address change did not notify the issuing bank, did not receive the bill, resulting in unpaid bills. The sooner you know these questions are more helpful for loan applications. There are other people who do not know the mortgage pre-approval.<br />\r\nThe mortgage pre-approval application is for free. For the first time to buy a house in Canada, professional opinion is very important. An experienced, insightful mortgage broker can let the borrower take a lot of detours. Some problems are often ignored by the Chinese, but in Canada&#39;s financial and legal system is a big problem. One of the most serious question is the down payment. Most of the Chinese need to transfer the down payment from China to Canada. Deposit period and transaction record are very important and therefore need to be prepared in advance.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="new-customtext">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext"><strong>Application materials</strong></h4>\r\n<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\nBefore mortgage pre-approval application, customers will know mortgage products are provided by banks. Customers will know whether the short-term or long-term mortgage products are more suitable for them.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Employer letter: need to use the company&#39;s letterhead, to include the name, position, total tax wages (annual income) and the company&#39;s working years.<br />\r\n2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If the self-employed, you need three years of financial statements, tax application form (together with the Inland Revenue Department&#39;s tax rebate).<br />\r\n3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Social Insurance number<br />\r\n4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Home Address (more than three years), and work experience(more than three years).<br />\r\n5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bank information (name of bank, address, type of account, and account name)<br />\r\n6)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Total assets and value (such as: cash, stocks, bonds, RRSP, vehicle)<br />\r\n7)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Total liabilities (eg, car loan, limit of credit card)<br />\r\n8)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Credit report\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Pre-approval', 1, 0),
(33, 'Small Business', 'Loan', '\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-6" style="margin-top:30px">\r\n<h4><strong>Small business loan include: </strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>1. The total annual income is not more than 5 million, unlimited, limited company, individual, partnership business can apply.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Business in Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Loans must be used in business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Business can not be farm, charity, religious organization.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-6" style="margin-top:30px">\r\n<h4><strong>Small business loans can not be used: </strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>1 Working capital</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2 Franchise fees</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3 Appraisal and legal costs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4 Goodwill</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5 Inventory</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-6" style="margin-top:30px">\r\n<h4><strong>Loan funds are based on invoices for expenses. There are three ways: </strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Directly to the supplier.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. To the lawyer, by the lawyer to control the use of loans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Invoice for payment. For example: you have decoration $70,000, ice library $20,000, dining table $10,000, a total of 10 million invoices, banks will give you $90,000 of the loan based on those invoices.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-6" style="margin-top:30px">\r\n<h4><strong>Small business loans note:</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Government guarantee fee is 2% of the loan amount.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. The use of loans has strict requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Approval has certain requirements. Chain business, especially the famous chain business, will easier get business loans.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-12" style="margin-top:30px">\r\n<h4><strong>Interest in small business loans, interest and other expenses: </strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;1. The term of the loan is related to the life of your business assets, but not more than 10 years. For example, your loan is used to buy pizza oven which life is 5 years, and your loan period is 5 years; if you buy a retail property and expect to do 30 years of business, but your loan life is not more than 10 years. The lender will arrange a monthly payment plan for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;2. Loan rates are variable and fixed. The interest rate is determined by the bank, usually around 6%, and the interest is shared by the bank and the government.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;3. Government registration fee is 2% of the amount of loans. For example, the bank grants you the amount of 100,000 loans, and ultimately you will get 98,000. The bank has approved your small business loan and does not mean you can spend it at will.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-md-12" style="margin-top:30px">\r\n<p>The most important thing about doing business is how to solve the shortage of funds. Buy a house can be 90% of loans, buy business can also be 90% of loans; business loans need to audit the profitability of business. People always thought that the strict requirements of business loans, procedures cumbersome difficult to grant down, it is not true. If your business (especially chain business) has a good income, the loan is not as difficult as you think. Small business is an important part of the Canadian economy, the most difficult thing for small business is funds. Canada Small Business Financing Loan is to help those who want to do business but lack of funds. According to the small business loan project, you can lend 90%, and the maximum loan amount does not exceed 1 million. Small business loan project is the government commissioned by banks and other financial institutions to implement. The government does not accept any application, do not participate in any approval, and the decision is entirely financial institutions. Major banks have small business loans and audit conditions. The bank staff will review the business you want to invest and your business plan. After agreeing to the loan, the loan will be registered in the Industry Canada. The small business loan program encourages the financial institution to give you the loan, the risk of the loan is taken by the government and the individual, the government assumes 75%, and the individual assumes 25%.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', 'Small Business', 1, 0),
(34, 'Exchange', 'Financial', '<div class="col-sm-4">\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext">Curreny Exchange</h4>\r\n\r\n<hr /><img class="img-responsive" src="/images/exchange/1.jpg" style="height: 262px;margin-top: 15px;margin-bottom: 15px;border-bottom-width: 10px; " />\r\n<p>1.) Main business of Monest Group is foreign currency trading.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-top: 30px;margin-bottom: 55px;">2.) Foreign exchange (Canadian, US, British pound, Swiss franc, Japanese yen and many other foreign currencies need to refer to the restrictions) * Spot and forward transactions</p>\r\n\r\n<hr /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-4">\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext">Exchange Rate</h4>\r\n\r\n<hr /><img class="img-responsive" src="/images/exchange/2.jpg" style="height: 262px;margin-top: 15px;margin-bottom: 15px;border-bottom-width: 10px;" />\r\n<p>1.) Exchange services of Monest Group by the experts will often track the best foreign exchange rates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2.) According to the needs of customers to provide the best choice for several foreign currency exchange.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3.) Foreign exchange experts in accordance with the needs of each customer to assist in the purchase of foreign assets or one-time exchange business.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-4">\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext">Rules</h4>\r\n\r\n<hr /><img class="img-responsive" src="/images/exchange/3.jpg" style="height: 262px;margin-top: 15px;margin-bottom: 15px;border-bottom-width: 10px;" />\r\n<p>1.) To conduct business as required by Canadian federal laws and regulations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2.) More than 3,000 dollars in cash transactions, customers must issue a valid identity document or valid documents.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr /></div>\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Exchange', 1, 0),
(35, 'Financial Investment', 'Financial', '\r\n<center>\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext">Investment and financial introduction:</h4>\r\n</center>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInvestment and financial management refers to the investors through reasonable arrangements for the use of funds such as savings, banking and financial products, bonds, funds, stocks, futures, commodity spot, foreign exchange, real estate, insurance, gold, P2P, culture and art investment and financial tools to individuals , The family and enterprises and institutions to manage the assets and distribution, to achieve the purpose of value-added, thereby accelerating the growth of assets. Investment and financial management, the earliest seen in the early 1990s, &quot;financial&quot; concept gradually popular.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1, financial management is a lifetime of money, not to solve the urgent problem of money only, but a sustainable cycle of the process.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2, financial management is the cash flow management, each person is born with the need for money (cash outflow), also need to make money to generate cash inflows, so no matter whether the money, everyone needs financial management.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n3, financial management also covers risk management. Because there are more uncertainties in the future, including personal risk, property risk and market risk, cash inflows (revenue disruptions) or cash outflows (incremental risk) are affected.</p>\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Financial Investment', 1, 0),
(36, 'Financial Trusts', 'Financial', '\r\n<h3 class="simple">What is Financial Trusts</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A trust is a fiduciary relationship in which one party, known as a trustor, gives another party, the trustee, the right to hold title to property or assets for the benefit of a third party, the beneficiary. In finance, it can also be a type of closed-end collective investment fund built as a public limited company.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3 class="simple">Basic principle</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A trust is a relationship whereby property is held by one party for the benefit of another. A trust is created by a settler, who transfers property to a trustee. The trustee holds that property for the trust&#39;s beneficiaries.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3 class="simple">Protection by Law</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A trust may have multiple trustees, and these trustees are the legal owners of the trust&#39;s property, but have a fiduciary duty to beneficiaries and various duties, such as a duty of care and a duty to inform. If trustees do not adhere to these duties, they may be removed through a legal action.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Financial Trusts', 1, 0),
(37, 'Venture Capital', 'Financial', '<center>\r\n<h5 style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Raleway; font-weight: 700; line-height: 24px; color: rgb(5, 70, 0);\r\n								margin: 0px 0px 15px; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;"><!--?php echo $page_title; ?-->Introduction</h5>\r\n</center>\r\n\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext">What is Venture Capital</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 1em 0px; display: block; unicode-bidi: embed; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13.92px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">　　<b style="margin: 0px; font-weight: bolder;">Venture capital</b> is financing that investors provide to start-up companies and small businesses that are believed to have long-term growth potential.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 1em 0px; display: block; unicode-bidi: embed; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13.92px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">　　Venture capital firms or funds invest in these early-stage companies in exchange for equity&ndash;an ownership stake&ndash;in the companies they invest in. Venture capitalists take on the risk of financing risky start-ups in the hopes that some of the firms they support will become successful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 1em 0px; display: block; unicode-bidi: embed; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13.92px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">　　Such investments are risky as they are illiquid, but are capable of giving impressive returns if invested in the right venture. The returns to the venture capitalists depend upon the growth of the company. Venture capitalists have the power to influence major decisions of the companies they are investing in as it is their money at stake.</p>\r\n', '', '', 'Venture Capital', 1, 0),
(38, 'Debt Consolidation Loans', 'Financial', '\r\n<div class="maintext">\r\n<p>We understand what you may be going through. We are here to listen and help you. All of our clients receive our utmost attention and complete confidentiality. Consolidating your debts is nothing to be embarrassed about.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext">Debt Consolidation Loans</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Debt consolidation is an ideal solution for people who can&rsquo;t afford to make several payments each month. We help replace them with one easy-to-track low monthly payment. Generally, they also have lower interest rates than what your creditors charges. Therefore, each month you are saving more and paying less. This is especially beneficial if you have credit card debt in Canada.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext">Why do I want to consolidate my debts?</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>People like debt consolidation because it makes their life easier: Easier cash budgeting, with one predictable monthly payment instead of several. Lower payments, because a debt consolidation loan often has a lower interest rate than unsecured debts such as credit card accounts. Lower payments, because a debt consolidation loan may have extended terms.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext">Do I qualify for a Debt Consolidation loan?</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Apply to a bank, or other lender, with enough support to make them feel confident that you will repay the loan. To make your case, you will need to provide: Your monthly budget, showing that you can afford the loan payments. Evidence that you have enough income to make the payments. This could be your pay stubs, for example. Extra security, either collateral (perhaps your house or car) or a co-signer.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4 class="new-customtext">Debt Consolidation Program Advantages</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>A debt consolidation program can reduce your monthly payments. A debt consolidation program can give you a head start on credit repair. A debt consolidation program can prevent you from making payments late. With a debt consolidation program you can get the expert help you need to get your finances back on track. A debt consolidation program will prevent creditors from harassing you or pursuing legal action.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Debt Consolidation Loans', 1, 0);
